I find power in the idea that certain people only know what I choose to allow them to see about myself. There are few people who get 100% access to me. As I get older I get more and more protective of my energy. I used to allow everyone access to the deepest parts of me only to find myself in a puddle of disappointment, distrust & anxiety. I don’t trust easily, but when I do, know that it’s full of loving, pure, genuine intentions. Not to say that I don’t enjoy socializing and meeting new people. I do. I’m somewhat of an introverted extrovert and I’ve learned to embrace that. When I love, I love deeply. I’ve let too many situations and people drain me to my core, to the point of me not even recognizing my own reflection in the mirror. Spread love, be a light, and 
protect yourself in the process. 💭 ✨

TOP SHELF IS DROPPING THIS FRIDAY 1/27! 

#newmusic #newmusicfriday #soulfunk #topself #newartist #pop #singersongwriter

Top Shelf ✨ is just the beginning of me finding a place in the music industry. Coming from someone who has been pushing through this industry basically her whole life, I have experienced very high highs and very low lows. Specifically in the world of music, it has been very hard to find good humans to work with that are just as dope of a creative. I found that in @thewildcardz. We truly had so much fun creating this one together. I am psyched to continue releasing music that makes me feel good. It’s not easy being an independent artist and navigating through the chaos on your own. If you dig this, it would mean the world if you’d share it with your friends, on your socials, like it on Spotify, comment your favorite part below and anything else that comes to mind! I see it all and it is so deeply appreciated. LINK IN BIO! 🤍

focused. 📸: @chrisjonphotography

STORYTIME: In 2019 I was in my bedroom in Los Angeles and I wrote a song called “Wrong Places.” At the time I was in a very weird place in my life and felt super lost. Around the same time I had just started listening to H.E.R’s EP “I Used To Know Her” on REPEAT. Fast forward to 2020, I found out that I was chosen to go on a show called @nbcsongland I had no idea what artist I’d be pitching to until I landed in LA and had my first meeting with the production team. The moment I found out it was H.E.R I lost it inside. I met so many talented songwriters on that show and got to work with the incredible @ryantedder as well as meeting @shanemcanally & @esterdean It was a huge turning point for me in this industry as I was very close to throwing everything in the towel and calling it quits. I’m very grateful I didn’t and for that experience. Timing is everything. It’s crazy how when you look back, manifestations turn up in the most mind boggling ways. Be super intentional on what/who you surround yourself with. Stay focused. Stay grateful. Follow that dream. @hermusicofficial thank you for taking this song and making a dreamers dream come true. Shoutout to the homie @zprunsthis who played the original guitar on the demo. Shoutout to @macariwines for my fav 🍷 Thank you to @thewildcardz for being incredible as always 🤍✨ #songwriter #singer #her #songland #wrongplaces
